The Kenyan government, has gone ahead to assure Cuban doctors, serving in various counties of their safety, just a day after two of their colleagues were abducted, during a brazen daylight attack which left one security officer dead, in Mandera county. National police service spokesperson, Charles Owino, revealed that a high level security meeting involving a multi?agency government team, had on Saturday morning met, and resolved to consolidate efforts in rescuing the medics, who are believed to be inside Somalia.